# TypeScript + Next.js Standards

- TypeScript: strict mode ON. Avoid `any`. Prefer zod schemas for API payload validation.
- Next.js App Router.
- Keep components small; prefer server components by default, client components only when needed.
- Styling: pick ONE approach and be consistent (e.g., Tailwind).
- Error handling:
  - All provider calls must return typed, structured errors.
  - UI must display actionable error messages (no raw stack traces).

Code changes:
- Small diffs. Prefer incremental commits. If change >300 LOC, split into multiple PR-sized chunks.
